###  https://dataout.org/ontology#queerVenue
:queerVenue rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                     <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept> ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> :publicAction ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#inScheme> :TriggerObjectCategoryScheme ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note> "We introduced this category to indicate cases of persecution against legal and natural persons associated with queer venues. In such cases, there is usually not a single trigger object indicated, but the fact that a venue is intended for LGBTQIA+ people serves as a trigger. This category can be seen as a subcategory of a public action. Note that this category does not indicate a (type of) physical place."@en ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Queer venue"@en ;
            <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q64364539> .


